    "body": "### Problem\n\nClangd return an error while typing with message: \"the file in non valid UTF-8\", the error keep at the same line even when deleting the entire line with **dd**.\n\nthat keep the lsp frozen even when executing cmds like **:LspRestart** or **:LspStop**\n\nwhen i changed the lspconfig from:\n``` lua\nrequire(\"nvchad.configs.lspconfig\").defaults()\n\nlocal servers = { \"html\", \"cssls\", \"clangd\" }\nvim.lsp.enable(servers)\n\n-- read :h vim.lsp.config for changing options of lsp servers\n```\nto:\n``` lua\nrequire(\"nvchad.configs.lspconfig\").defaults()\n\nlocal servers = { \"html\", \"cssls\" }\nvim.lsp.enable(servers)\n\nlocal lspconfig = require \"lspconfig\"\nlspconfig.clangd.setup {\n  cmd = { \"clangd\", \"--header-insertion=never\" },\n}\n\n-- read :h vim.lsp.config for changing options of lsp servers\n```\n\nit work!\n\nthis error just appear with the new vim.lsp...\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nUsing NVchad:\n lua\n │configs\n │ │  conform.lua\n │ │  lazy.lua\n │ └  lspconfig.lua   <----- here is the lspconfig file\n  plugins\n │ └  init.lua\n │  chadrc.lua\n │  mappings.lua\n └  options.lua\n  .stylua.toml\n  init.lua\n  lazy-lock.json\n  LICENSE\n  README.md\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n_No response_\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.1\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nclangd version 19.1.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 10 22H2\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
