            "body": "I think this is an issue with the capabilities property on the default config when using vim.lsp.enable,\nand with custom config i remove the capabilities field and it work.\n\nin default the capabilities configuration is:\n``` lua\n  - capabilities: {\n      general = {\n        positionEncodings = { \"utf-8\", \"utf-16\", \"utf-32\" }\n      },\n    }\n```\n\nand if i do it with the classic way:\n``` lua\nrequire('lspconfig').clangd.setup {}\n```\ni can just remove the capabilities and live it just with cmd",
